Planit are world leaders in application testing and quality engineering. We
provide solutions that support organisations to deliver high quality systems,
applications, and IT architecture.

Planit is now a proud NRI company and part of a global movement to deliver a
sustainable and secure future through better Information Technology exchanges.
Our team offer expert consultancy, bespoke services, tailored training and
unique solutions to complex projects. Specialising in digital quality, Planit
have a geographic footprint across many continents, with 1700+ permanent
employees and have been recognised in Gartner's Magic Quadrant for Application
Testing Services.

Our values and ethos are focused on an intrinsic connection to our people, the
awareness of our environment and our pursuit to be better than yesterday. We
continue to lead the industry with unrivalled ideas, ability, and a quest to
discern paradigms.

** About The Role: **

As a Senior Automation Consultant, you will consult to our top tier client
base to develop and deliver high calibre solutions. The role will be a mixture
of onsite technical strategic delivery and operational leadership. The role
will require you to work with account directors and business development teams
to provide technical guidance on proposals. Additionally, you will assist with
staff mentoring, development, recruitment support, and global innovation
projects. This is a technical role requiring a strong development background,
an understanding of DevOps concepts such as CI/CT/CD and Infrastructure as
Code as well as proven experience in designing modern automation solutions
using both open source and commercial tools.

** Responsibilities: **

  * Drive internal initiatives to foster a collaborative innovation and learning culture 
  * Analyse, design, build scalable and robust quality engineering solutions both internally for Planit and our clients in the areas of: Automation Engineering, Agile, CI/CD, Continuous Testing, DevOps, Cloud Engineering (AWS / Azure / GCP) 
  * Manage stakeholder expectations, keeping them informed throughout the project. 
  * Work closely with the Sydney leadership team and global practice leads 
  * Work across multiple clients delivering strategic and tactical solutions and pre-sales work 
  * Run and participate in monthly automation challenges 
  * Running workshops and training as part of our overall L&D program 

** Essential Skills and Experience: **

  * Strong demonstrated experience working within Automation Testing 
  * A proven track record in managing successful teams 
  * A solid understanding of Object-Oriented development practices 
  * Experienced in delivering high quality test automation solutions with tools such as Selenium, Cypress.io, Playwright etc. 
  * Hands on experience with CI/CD tools such as Jenkins, Bamboo, Azure DevOps, GoCD, Circle CI etc. 
  * Hands on experience with Docker 
  * BDD with tools such as Cucumber, SpecFlow, JBehave 
  * Version control with GIT and a good understanding of branching and merging 
  * Demonstrated ability to solve technical problems and implement innovative solutions 

If you have only ever recorded test automation scripts, this isn't the role
for you! You must know how to architect and develop highly scalable, robust
and maintainable solutions and lead successful teams and projects within
traditional, Agile and scaled Agile environments.

